BeliefsOpen: It's a positive experience because I spend a lot of time with other people, so when I get alone time it means that I can finally have some time to myself to gather my thoughts and think, and stick to my own interests and things I enjoy doing. It gives me time to recharge mentally for my social/family interactions, and helps me destress. I am surrounded by people all the time so I don't feel negatively when I'm alone.

I think spending time alone is okay as you get your own time your self and you can switch off from the world. For example, you can play video games, study or watch a movie without other people bothering you.
Sometimes it does get lonely and can have a negative effect however aslong as u keep busy, it can be positive.

I enjoy spending time alone to an extent, and I have recently started doing solo activities like going to the theatre and the cinema alone, so that has definitely improved my alone time. I do have times though where I really need human interaction and get quite lonely if I do spend too much time alone so I think a balance is needed.
Spending time alone, allows me to go through my thoughts and take care of my self.

Spending time alone allows me to pursue my own hobbies and interests and to recharge. Being comfortable spending time along means that I spent more valuable time with others and with people that are more valuable to me.
indifferent - dont love it and dont hate it
I like to be alone sometimes as it allows me to be left alone with my thoughts and i get to relax without thinking of anyone. the only downside is it can sometimes get lonely

I usually find alone time a positive experience to engage in activities I enjoy e.g. watching a film or going to the gym. However, if I am feeling anxious or lonely then being alone can increase the strength of these feelings and then it can be a more negative experience.

Spending time alone is a positive experience for me. I get to do what I want, when I want, without having to think of anyone else or please anyone else. I don't have to worry about another persons feelings and I get to spend that time alone. I thoroughly enjoy spending time alone.

I enjoy spending time alone as I am naturally an introvert, and I experience burn out as a result of my customer service job. However, I often feel lonely and isolated when I spend a long time alone. At the moment, it is negatively affecting my mental health

spending time alone is a positive experience because it allows to me to self reflect and become more comfortable in my own company,

Could also be a negative experience if it was to happen to often as you could develop bad social habbits when in larger groups in the future.

Positive because i am able to do my own things when, what and how i want. this without been decided when i am allowed to or not, like my mum asking me to do something straight away when i just want to relax and ill do it later
I feel completely unmotivated and my internal clock shifts the more time I spend alone (e.g. wake up at midday and sleep at 4am instead of a more usual schedule).

For me it's a positive thing. I can do what I want, when I want. I get to enjoy the peace of my surroundings and don't feel pressured to do things with others. 

I'm generally introverted anyway, so being alone for long periods lets me do the things I like and without the need to be constantly on the go.

I find it to be an overall positive experience. I overthink a lot in social situations about how I'm perceived by others, and it is very draining. Even if I'm with friends, I find myself wishing to be alone pretty soon. I think this is heavily influenced by my depression, but they definitely feed into each other. In my alone time, I don't have to answer to anyone and can zone out if I need to. However, I do feel isolated and lonely generally; I actually feel this more when I'm not alone.

I enjoying spending time alone, it helps me unwind and relax and think about things without interruption, but after a couple. Of days then it becomes lonely and boring but I do find that day alone is massively benificial
I think a balance is good, alone time for self reflection and development and socialisation for personal growth and building relationships

Being alone is a negative experience as you’re stuck in your own thoughts. You can not get another opinion or there is no one there to cheer you up or encourage you. It is all down to you which can be difficult.

I have absolutely awful social anxiety, I don't have good experiences with having friends, when I'm alone I'm in control. All my things are around me, the hobbys I enjoy, my pets, I don't have to acquiese to other peoples will and their wants. I can do exactly what I want when I want it.

I think spending time alone is good to relax and disengage and I personally can get overwhelmed being around others sometimes. I can also do what I want when I'm alone such as read or watch whatever I want to without people complaining.

I gain energy from being alone and being able to do creative things or reading books. that said i enjoy having my animals around me, but not people!!
to me being around people is tiring and being alone is how i best recover and gain energy to be around people again.

i love being alone a lot but that said I don't want to be completely alone always!
I think everyone should have alone time, it’s good just to be with you thoughts and no one to disturb you or get on your nerves
I like spending time alone because I can do what I want and relax in my own space, which is healthy.
I love being alone time to think time to read my books I love reading and sitting the garden with a cuppa
It's not really anything to me, it's just an experience.  I have no emotions associated with it.

Spending time alone is nice in moderation. It's nice to recharge my social battery and have time to relax and unwind but it can become sad and lonely if I'm alone too much so it's both positive and negative.

Spending time alone can be really beneficial for me as it gives me a chance to reflect, grow personally, and relax mentally. It also boosts my creativity and helps me understand myself better. However, if I spend too much time alone, I sometimes feel lonely and isolated, so I try to maintain a balance by ensuring I also have meaningful social interactions.

I enjoy spending time alone because I can be very overstimulated by external noise and activity. So I rely on alone time to gather my thoughts and keep myself centred. Time by myself boosts my mood as I don't have to give any of myself - I find it restful and important to my mental health.
In the most I can enjoy being alone and doing what I want to do, when I want. Being around other people, although enjoyable, invariable leads to a degree of compromise.

i enjoy spending time alone so it is a positive experience for me. it gives me the opportunity to do my hobbies uninterrupted and to be myself. i don't feel comfortable being around other people so it leads to a lot of anxiety. when i am alone i don't have to worry about what other people think of me.
It is a negative experience for me because it is so often, and I don’t have any friends and am desperately, sadly lonely

I find being alone a generally positive experience. I can sometimes find it mentally draining being around other people, including my friends and family. I find that I can recharge my batteries when I'm on my own where I can do whatever I want, when I want.
I do like time alone. I like to feel quiet in my mind which i can at times. Other times I find being alone uncomfortable. It depends very much on my mood and how things are going in my life.

Time alone is generally positive for me as I enjoy peace and quiet and doing my own things
I lived alone for a long time before I met my husband
I do miss him when he goes away though (sometimes he has work trips)

It depends on my mood and what i have going on. If i am in a good space and in a good mood being on my own is a positive. I can relax, do what i want and just chill out. If i am not in a good mental space, this will cause me to overthink and ruminate which is not so good. I am quite independent so being on my doesn't phase me but it is noticeable as i have a busy job and life.
It is a positive as it allows me to relax and think about things in peace but it can be isolating at times so it's important to have a good balance

i enjoy spending time alone it gives me time to do things for myself and what i want without thinking of others. it gives me chance to do all the little jobs for myself i wouldn't normally do if other people are around me.  I think everyone needs me time.

Spending time alone whilst working at home, doing jobs around the house or garden, or whilst out exercising or shopping is mostly a positive experience as I can get on with what I need to do without restriction. Other time alone such as evenings and weekends is more of a negative experience as I would like to spend time with people sharing an experience and having time to chat.

I am an introvert so it allows me time to recharge. It also allows me to reflect on thoughts and feelings and do activities that I enjoy doing on my own, like cleaning, watching YouTube, writing my diary...
In order to have some type of self confidence, you need to spend time with yourself. It is important for you to get to know yourself in order for you to even begin loving yourself.

Broadly I don't mind being alone and when I have been with others a while I really appreciate some alone time. I find being alone peaceful and a chance to work on myself and my thoughts. However it can be isolating and lonely at times. However as little as 30 minutes of interaction with friends is enough to solve that.

Overall I'd say I find spending time alone more positive than the average person.

sometimes being alone is fine especially if you have had family around you all the time or had a very hard day at work and just need some time to be alone and chill doing little or just to have time for yourself

Being alone isn't necessarily a good or bad experience- it's the state of mind that I'm in that matters. I like my own company and find that being around others for too long is exhausting, so I like being alone sometimes to help me relax, and I can only really get things done when I'm not with friends (work colleagues are different, you have to be around them). If I'm upset or not in a good mood, sometimes being alone is the last thing I need and can exacerbate the negative emotions I'm feeling.
I don't feel it is positive or negative - it is just how my life is, my normal, and its just how things are.

Spending time alone is fine to me as I enjoy my own company and don't have a lot of trust in other people. Some times in my life being alone can be a negative experience, and other times it can be positive. It depends on my state of mind and maybe slightly other factors like events taking place at that time in my life
I think it's a positive experience, my wife and I both work from home and it can be stressful at times due to workload so being alone is good. It is also good to be alone with your own thoughts.

It can be a mix of both. Sometimes I think it is healthy to be alone and have time for ourselves to enjoy simple things like a bath or reading a book, it is good to be comfortable in your own company. However at other times it can be a very negative experience that makes you feel miserable and lonely and has a bad affect on your mental health.

Spending time alone can be positive as it provides time for reflection. Often when we are with others we are focused on them and not ourselves.

Time alone can also be negative as sometimes it creates a cycle of loneliness and starts producing negative thinking
I need to be alone sometimes to practice meditation or to concentrate on work.

I enjoy being alone for short amounts of time, I get to do what i want to do without having to think of others. I can change my own plans depending on my mood, or what needs doing etc. But longer than a few hours and I feel incredibly lonely, i feel isolated and it seems my brain forgets about anyone else, i usually seek comfort by messaging my partner etc.

As a busy working mum of two young boys when i finally get chance to be alone i enjoy it but i am well aware that that is because it is out of the ordinary for me to have time by myself.

I would not like too much alone time.
i enjoy my time alone, doing exactly what i want to do.  Although I think it is only a positive experience because I know that at a later time I will have my spouse or children to spend time with.

I work from home so I spend a lot of time on my own and I personally absolutely love it. I like to be able to do things on my watch and make decisions about how to spend my day (i.e working/going out etc) all around my energy, which can really vary day to day. My stress levels since being at home more has decreased significantly, so I would definitely say being alone is a positive experience for me.

I really enjoy being alone and would generally choose to be alone. However, I often feel better when I have spent time with close family and so I am not sure if my choice to be alone is based around feelings of anxiety or habit. When I am alone I feel much more in control of my time.
i prefere feeling alone alone than feeling alone with people

I feel i spend too much time alone. I lack any real hobbies so therefore alone time results in me being bored and sedentary. I'm a very outdoors person and a lot of the activities I enjoy, such as photography, require good weather conditions. Most of my friends also don't share this passion to the extent i do which makes companionship in this hobby difficult. Overall, i think this has a negative experience on my life.

I'm generally ok with spending time alone, I don't have any problem finding ways to occupy my time whether or not other people are around me.  So overall being alone is positive for me.  I've always felt this way - it's not that I dislike spending time with others, far from it, but I don't need to spend time with others to be happy.  I think this is because we're all basically wired to be one way or another at a genetic level and so some people can't stand being alone because of how they are at a level that is not learned behavior.
I enjoy being alone for a certain amount of time but am also lucky in having family living with me.  I would not like to be on my own all the time

I enjoy spending time alone, it gives me a chance to relax and switch off and not have to think of others.  I can also do whatever I want and enjoy myself in the process.  So for me it is a positive experience.

I enjoy spending time alone as i'm fairly independent with hobbies that can be carried out solo. For example surfing, bouldering, calisthenics and gaming. Although i can do these activities independently i do enjoy spending time with others doing these and other things. Despite this i'm still more than happy to do things on my own to enjoy the experience with or without friends there so i don't miss out on the opportunities that present themselves. Even if they would be more enjoyable sharing them with someone else its better to have the experience rather than not. I think time alone is positive for reflection and self fulfilment and enjoyment but too much time alone leads to social isolation and negativity.

As am getting older I'm better at spending time alone ...I have a really busy life as a teacher andthe time I spend alone in the garden or walking I use it to contemplate my life and try and meditate a bit 
It seems to help me focus and remain grateful for what I have

Spending time alone is enjoyable for me as I am happy with my own company. I can read or watch TV without worrying about anyone else. It also gives me a chance to be alone with my thought and to unwind.
I feel spending time on my own is a positive thing. I appreciate the lack of pressure to engage with other people, I am fortunate that I enjoy my own company and I always have something to occupy me.

I rarely spend time alone, as I am a full time carer. So when I do get a few hours, it gives me a chance to do whatever I want in peace. I can watch what I want on TV, listen to music, tidy up without someone getting in my way, read a book in peace, go for a walk. I love to have time on my own and greatly look forward to it.

I am struggling with my time alone at the moment because of recent changes/disruptions to my social circle and work life and home life - a confluence of losing the majority of my regular social contacts in a short space of time. Normally I'm quite happy with my solitude and alone time because it was balanced with fulfilling social contact time and connections with very close friends to acquaintances. Having lost all that, my alone time is much greater and feels more challenging.

When I had more social connections, I actually get socially burned out quite easily/low social battery which is why I really value my individual time/downtime. But the change in the wider context of my life has changed that. The alone time I most enjoy is spent in nature - in my garden, on walks, when I feel connected to wildlife (birds and insects, trees, waterways, plants and flowers) - or being productive with creative/practical things (DIY, gardening, cooking, art). I like reading and I enjoy watching TV alone. I CANNOT watch films alone and don't care for eating alone, it makes it feel very functional/basic. I enjoy meditation/yoga and like to do that alone as much as I like to practice in a shared space. But at the moment, I struggle to enjoy any of these solitary pursuits because they aren't balanced by positive social connection time the way they used to be.

I would much rather be alone. I have a busy time with my family and I work as a music teacher. Being alone and quiet is a joy. I am also very happy to do any activity that I enjoy alone, I can go to the cinema or theatre and be alone and that is fine with me, I do not miss out. Most of the time I do not enjoy the company of other people. The conversations are limited to food and weather and never anything deeper.

I find that being alone allows me to truly be myself and that I can properly relax and not worry about how I am being percieved by others. I enjoy feeling relaxed and calm when I am alone so I find it to be a positive experience. I can explore my interests without feeling pressured by others to alter how I am acting or what I enjoy. However, I enjoy being with my partner and feel like I can be myself around them. I often feel the same way when I am with my partner as when I am alone.

Mostly I enjoy being alone - which is a good thing, as I am disabled and at home alone almost all day for 5 days of the week. I prefer the quiet, and have things I enjoy doing - reading, sewing, painting, gardening, cooking, minor d.i.y. 

I do miss company and conversation - and work. 

Sometimes I get lonely, especially when I am particularly ill (I have M.E.) as I don't have enough energy to talk to people on the phone, or to do the things I enjoy. Then it is a negative experience.

I quite enjoy spending time alone and usually don't see it as a negative experience. I feel like I need quiet, alone time each day, especially if I've been socialising/ talking to people at work. It's not that I find being sociable challenging or negative, but I feel like I always need to counterbalance it with time spent by myself afterwards. I think I have become more inclined this way the older I've got.

I feel positive when I am alone, for the most part. My hobbies are quiet, lone hobbies, like reading, and sewing, and they fulfil me. I find I'm in such a state of flow when i'm doing these things that I don't notice that I'm alone. I do spend almost all of my time with my pets, so I think that makes a difference energetically. But I find other humans quite draining. I also find it difficult to find people I can truly be myself with, so it's easier to be alone, and more fulfilling. Sometimes I feel lonely, but not often, and I'm more likely to feel lonely around the wrong people than I am when I'm alone
I think it's positive as I am able to reflect and relax. I like being able to think about whatever I want, or not think at all and not have to make conversation.
It allows me to be myself without having to act a certain way. However, I think it is positive in moderation, as we all need social interaction to some degree.

Most of the time, spending time alone is a largely positive experience. I'm an introvert, so being with other people tires me out mentally and physically. If someone asks me to spend time with them, it ruins my day more than helps it. I also have social anxiety, so being alone is helpful for that too. Overall, it's peaceful. Sometimes the loneliness can turn into boredom, but I'd rather that than be with others.

I like being alone as i work full time, having 2 sons aged 13 yrs and 8 yrs. I also have a husband so i would say the only time i am alone is on the school run to work and then vice a versa. I like the fact i can just switch off and watch something without interruptions or even just read. I like i can listen watch what i want, at times i dont feel i want to talk but when your with othe rpeople you feel you need to talk

Spending time alone for me is a positive experience. I find that time away from noise and distraction helps my mental health and allows me to switch off from the stresses of day to day life. Having alone time helps me be a better person when I am around other people.

I generally find it a positive experience as I can feel overwhelmed being in a large group. It gives me chance to think peacefully. However, i do like being with others and can feel lonely when I spend too much time alone.
Positive experience. It is good to be alone and enjoy time by yourself, as much as it is to spend it and connect with others. When you are connected to yourself, you can enjoy being by yourself.
i sometimes enjoy being alone as it as i often just prefer my own company and enjoy the quiet, it allows thought process etc

I enjoy alone time and am happy with my own company and always have been. I am married, but it is still important for me to have personal time, which I do. I use this time to indulge my personal interests and hobbies.
To me alone time is a positive experience.
I do enjoy my own company. However the option to not be alone is often preferable since I can become too comfortable with solitude.

I normally like spending time alone. It's nice to be able to think calmly about life, especially when making important decisions. I think there is a big difference between spending time alone and feeling alone, the latter is very isolating but doesn't necessarily require you to not be around other people.

Spending time alone is both a positive and negative experience for me. Both me and my partner work from home, so when he goes out and I am on my own it can give me time to think, be alone with my thoughts and catch up on my feelings. However, if I spend too much time alone I tend to overthink, and this can lead to me worrying, causing anxiety or other negative emotions which is a negative experience for me.

Generally I find time alone a positive experience being able to relax and focus on what I want to do - a break from other things. But, context is important - I am happily married and have lots of friends so being alone is different and generally a choice with the knowledge comfort of knowing it is temporary.
Having time alone does not bother me i can do what i want to do when i want to do something with just my own thoughts and no interruptions

I think it can be a positive or negative experience depending on what is happening in your life. If you are experiencing stressful times them being alone can feel very lonely without someone to share your fears or problems with. If you are content - alone time can be rewarding and peaceful. Being alone too much or not enough can be negative, I think you need some balance.
I enjoy my alone time as I find it to be exhausting being on other peoples company all the time.

Spending time alone can be a positive experience if you're trying to unwind and relax yourself by doing things you enjoy, and it can be exhausting to spend time with others all the time and planning out activities and travelling whereas being by yourself you got a lot more freedom

But it can be negative as well if you got no one to turn to or speak to so therefore you got no one but yourself to rely on
Sometimes it’s good to spend time alone to think to yourself and relax but other times you can feel lonely and miss companionship

I am a loner.  Never lonely. Live on my own, an independent, free, woman who does everything herself.  I can do what I want, whenever I want. Positive lifestyle choice on my part.  Hell is other people unfortunately and I am not prepared to live by anyone else’s rules.
Spending time alone is a positive experience for me. I am an introvert so spending time with people uses up my social battery, spending time alone gives me a chance to recharge it

Thanks to my atypical autism, being alone is essential for me to recover from the exhaustion of being around others.

Am I solitary by nature, or is it simply due to this imperative? Who knows, but I enjoy solitude.

For me, I think spending time alone is generally not a positive thing. I'm naturally introverted so I don't usually find company attractive. But in order to prevent me always being isolated. I try and push myself to be around another people. I've also noticed that if I isolate myself a lot then I start to have ignorant views about other people.

Being alone is okay for me in small doses, but if I spend too much time alone I find it to be very unpleasant. If I am alone for long periods, I struggle with the motivation to care for myself. I find it boring and struggle to feel proper joy without other people's company. It is nice to be alone when I have spent time in large crowds or meeting lots of strangers, as i find this draining and being alone can help me recharge from this.

I enjoy being alone quite often. Don't get me wrong, I love being in other peoples' company but sometimes my social battery runs out and I just want peace and quiet. When I'm along I read, or watch TV, or just potter about but it's important for me and allows me to gather my thoughts and reflect on different areas of my life. I think there's a difference between choosing to be alone and having solitude thrust upon you. Some people need company 24/7 but that's not for me. I think having the security of friends/family/a partner means I don't mind being alone as I can pick up the phone and see people whenever I want

I like to spend time alone because it allows me time to analysis what has been going on in my life lately. It gives me permission to reflect on positives and negatives. 
Being alone can be a negative experience, if I have experienced a lot of negative emotions in the last few weeks.

Spending time alone is something I have always done. I grew up in a family of 9, I always kept myself to myself and enjoyed being alone than included. The older I have gotten, I have appreciated being around people more but when I am alone I don't mind it. I guess as I always have enjoyed my own company, I don't really find it upsetting being on my own.

I find time alone to be a very positive experience. I like to have the space to make my own decisions on my own terms and have the time to reflect on whatever the pressing issues of the day are. I definitely find my mind refreshed if I take time for a solo bike ride.

Some times it is great to be alone with your own thoughts and have time to relax and just do what you want to do. Other times you may want company and it might not be available so one can feel a bit lonley. It is great when you have the choice of either.

I mostly enjoy being alone to collect my thoughts and enjoy the peace.

Sometimes being alone for to long can have a negative impact as I might get bored.

Spending time alone in the evenings is a positive experience for me.  I like to be left alone for a couple of hours to listen to music, catch up on emails etc.  I find this time is a bit like a re-set for me, and I often feel much calmer afterwards.  That said, I would not want to be alone all the time as I feel that I would think too much which would be a negative for me.

I do suffer from loneliness quite often, I am on my own all day until my partner comes home from work in the evening. I am very very shy and socially awkward, so the thought of spending time with other people is quite scary for me - my social skills are very rusty. I have lost all my confidence. I also think that spending some time alone is very good for rest and mental health, I think it's important too to just have a bit of me time. Spending a lot of time alone can be bad for my mental health too, I feel lonely at times and crave friendship, but at the same time I'm nervous pursuing friendships because I have been isolated so long and I don't have good social skills. It's a bit of a catch 22 situation for me.

I love spending time alone. I like to be on my own to gather my thoughts and reflect on different things. 

On the negative side, i think that due to my mental health issues, being alone can be negative as i think about things too much. I need to find the right balance.

I like spending time alone it gives me an opportunity to relax and prepare for when i next see people. However, if I spend too much time alone i get pretty lonely and more anxious because i start to dread interacting with others again.
I regard it as a positive experience as it gives me time to reflect on things, clear my mind and be in a calm state.

I feel spending time alone is enjoyable and positive because you get to have all the time you need, no disturbance or complaints. I also get to be self reliant and have no one dependent on me. People can be very weird in nature and I hope to avoid that part of them.

Spending a lot of time alone is a positive experience for me and is often how I live my day to day life. I find it absolutely exhausting to be around people, to have to try and figure out what their emotional state is, what they're like as a person and to work around that so that I don't come across as strange or weird. I'm also a people pleaser so when I'm around more than one or two people, I find myself doing everything I can to ensure that they're having a good time instead of focusing on wheher or not I'm having a good time myself. Being alone is my opportunity to refocus on myself, to recharge my batteries as it were and focus on the things that make me happy without wondering if I'm bothering anyone. It's always positive to me.
Being alone has never bothered me. I can occupy myself easily. I sometimes miss female company when alone for a period though...

I need time alone to recuperate and recharge, physically and mentally as I can feel very fatigued after doing my job (which involves a lot of interaction). That said,I like being around others, even if it's on the periphery. I find too much time alone isolating and it affects my self-esteem and can lead to feelings of low mood and anxiety. It's very much about striking the right balance.
Spending time alone is usually a bad idea for me because i already get way to much of it as an unemployed, single guy with no freinds so alone time is is just the same old negative force on my life
Spending time alone is positive if done for the right reason. To be away from noise, distractions and outside influences allows you to clear the mind. In a way, detox.

How I feel about being alone depends on what happened when I was last spending time with another person. If I had a positive time, then I feel fine about being by myself--I can work on a project, read, play a video game, without being disturbed or interrupted. I have social anxiety, and sometimes just someone being in the same room as me can prevent me from relaxing. 

If when I was recently spending time with another person the interaction went badly, then being alone becomes a very negative experience, as I have a tendency to spiral. I may begin to stew in my negative thoughts and be unable to break out of them, preventing me from being able to do much, if anything engaging. On some occasions I get the strong desire to drink heavily.
I have a busy life with children and work so I really enjoy time alone when I get it. I don't particularly enjoy social situations and fine they take a lot of my energy, so time alone feels peaceful.

I very much enjoy being by myself. I am married and a mum to two young children and a teacher. I am ALWAYS surrounded by others and I therefore cherish time in my own company. It is now a rare treat. 
I have always felt comfortable by myself. e.g. my friends know not to ask me to shop with them as I love to shop by myself and cannot stand shopping with others. 
I do love to meet up with friends and I always enjoy myself but it is the days that I have to myself that I really look forward to.

Positive
- can be self directed and spend time on things I want to spend time on
- free of noise and an opportunity for relaxation
- no obligations or social pressures to fulfil
- able to think my own thoughts without other people's opinions, ideas, feelings etc
- can 'be myself' more

Negative
- left with my own thoughts / feelings too long can lead to them being distorted 
- ideas and creative thoughts can only go so far without external input to advance or critique them
- I might end up in a loop, incapable of doing new things, without others'
- I forget to do some things without other people (eat, drink, sleep properly)

I think being alone is fine, I can occupy my own time with activities I like to do, gym, running, swimming, video games. All of which are fine alone and I wouldn't really ever do with friends. I do get lonely on my own, and often spend more time on my phone than I would like because of this. But I feel it's okay to be alone.
I enjoy it and see it as a positive as long as it's not all the time. You can relax and switch off from the world.

I enjoy my own company, however as someone who lives alone, I find it difficult not having someone close to me who I interact with regularly. My friends live a fair distance away and I feel like I am the one who always goes to see them. Everyone has their own lives and my feelings often go unnoticed, and I wouldn't want to draw attention to them.

Being comfortable whilst being alone is certainly not a bad thing, and many people find themselves more productive or more able to enjoy certain pursuits by themselves.  However, it needs to be a choice - forced loneliness can be a very negative thing.
I'm quite independent, i don't overly mind being alone and don't feel particularly affected when i am alone, but its nice having my partner here.
Due to my job I like spending time alone and not having to constantly talk. I can gather my thoughts and feelings and settle and re group with myself.

I have a busy job and a busy life so being alone is a luxury! I enjoy doing activities on my own such as going to the gym or going to the cinema or going for a coffee and just relaxing and people watch. It feels like self care. The question asks whether it's a positive OR negative but is flawed since it's both. In the short term spending time alone is generally useful for productivity, mindfulness, introspection and all sorts of things but humans are social creatures and thus some amount of time with others is essential for sanity's sake for most, if not all humans, including myself. Those are one of the whys for each way but I'm not sure what you're trying to accomplish and thus not sure how to answer more usefully.

I am 72 years old, much of my youth was spent in the bombed out ruins of Manchester. Being on your own wandering through the crofts and cellars of bombed out houses was great. A massive adventure. A voyage of discovery and wondering what became of the people that lived here.  Growing up through my teens was exactly the same, I enjoyed my own company, could do what I liked, with no commitments or having anothers opinions that I had to consider. My working life on building sites was the most I had to put with other people, but they reinforced my belief that being on my own was safer, more productive and better suited. I became self employed so worked alone, became a site manager so worked alone instructing as the job needed, I became a contracts manager and then contracts director. All my own doing. Spending time alone can be a bit of a mixed bag for me. On one hand, I do enjoy having some time to myself to unwind and recharge. I find that I can think more clearly and reflect on my thoughts and feelings without distractions. I also appreciate the opportunity to pursue my own interests and hobbies without anyone else's input or opinions. It's nice to have some quiet time to read a book, take a long bath, or watch a movie without anyone else's expectations.
On the other hand, I do sometimes feel a bit anxious or uneasy when I'm alone for too long. I worry that I'll get bored or restless, and I might start to feel like I'm missing out on social interactions and connections with others. I also sometimes struggle with negative self-talk and self-doubt when I'm alone, which can be hard to shake off.
I think a big part of how I feel about being alone is influenced by my personal circumstances. When I'm in a busy period at work or school, having some time alone can be a welcome respite from the chaos. But when I'm going through a tough time or feeling isolated from others, being alone can feel like a lonely and isolating experience.
Overall, I think spending time alone can be a positive experience for me if I use it as an opportunity to focus on my own growth and well-being. But it can also be challenging if I start to feel disconnected from others or like I'm stuck in my own thoughts.

For me at the current moment (as in, the last month or so), spending time alone is very common - most of my time is spent alone, with a smaller proportion of time spend in the vicinity of family members and only a very small amount of time spent with friends or acquaintances. Being alone largely feels like a positive experience for me. If I am alone, I can spend time researching and thinking about things that interest me or doing tasks without having to think about if the other person is enjoying themselves, having to look presentable (as in, hair, make-up, clothes, and facial expressions), devoting energy to keeping up conversations, etc. However, I am also aware that in the long-run, particularly as relates to interpersonal relationships and mental health, spending too much time alone can be detrimental. It impacts on friendships and makes it progressively harder to spend time around others, and also causes one to think less of others (probably inadvertently and without realising so) when one consistently values time alone over time with others.
Time alone lets you recharge your social battery to allow you to engage with others once you have company

Peace and Quiet: Time alone allows for a break from the hustle and bustle of daily life. It provides a quiet environment where I can relax, reflect, and recharge without external distractions.

Positive Aspects:

Peace and Quiet: Time alone often provides a respite from the hustle and bustle of daily life. It gives me a chance to enjoy peace and quiet, which can be incredibly refreshing and restorative.

Self-Reflection: Solitude allows for deep self-reflection. It provides an opportunity to think about my life, goals, and values without external distractions. This can lead to personal growth and a better understanding of myself.

Loneliness: There are times when being alone can feel isolating. If it stretches over long periods or if I’m already feeling down, solitude can exacerbate feelings of loneliness and sadness.

Overthinking: Too much alone time can sometimes lead to overthinking and rumination. Without the distractions of company, it's easy to get caught in negative thought patterns.

Why I View It This Way:

Balance: My perspective on being alone is shaped by a desire for balance. I recognize the need for solitude to recharge and reflect, but I also value social interactions and the support of others.

Past Experiences: My past experiences play a significant role. Positive experiences with solitude, like successful creative projects or peaceful moments of relaxation, reinforce the benefits. Conversely, times when I've felt isolated or overly introspective highlight the potential downsides.

Spending time alone can be a deeply personal and multifaceted experience, and people's perceptions of it often reflect their broader personality traits and life circumstances. Here’s a breakdown of how I see it:

Positive Aspects:

Self-Reflection and Growth: Time alone allows for introspection and personal growth. It’s an opportunity to reflect on one's goals, values, and experiences without external distractions. This can lead to greater self-awareness and clarity about one's life direction.
Creative Freedom: Being alone often provides a quiet environment that can foster creativity. Without the influence of others, one can explore ideas and projects freely, which is essential for innovation and personal expression.
Rest and Recharge: For many, solitude offers a chance to recharge mentally and emotionally. It can be a break from the social interactions and demands of daily life, helping to reduce stress and prevent burnout.
Negative Aspects:

Loneliness and Isolation: For some, being alone can lead to feelings of loneliness and isolation. This is particularly true if one is in a period of life where social connections are lacking or if they have a preference for constant social interaction.
Self-Criticism: Time alone might also bring up self-doubt or negative self-talk. Without the external feedback from others, one's inner critic might become more vocal, leading to a more challenging mental state.
Lack of Structure: For individuals who thrive on routine and interaction, time alone can feel aimless or unproductive, potentially leading to a sense of purposelessness or dissatisfaction.
In summary, whether time alone is perceived positively or negatively can depend on individual preferences, mental state, and the context in which the solitude occurs. It can be both a nurturing space for personal development and a challenging one, depending on one’s circumstances and mindset.

For me, spending time alone is a multifaceted experience that can be both positive and negative, depending on various factors and my mindset at the time. There are moments when solitude feels incredibly rejuvenating and peaceful. It allows me to recharge mentally and emotionally, offering a break from the constant stimulation of daily life. During these times, I cherish the opportunity to engage in activities that I find personally fulfilling, whether it's reading a book, practicing a hobby, or simply reflecting on my thoughts without external distractions.

On the other hand, there are instances when being alone can feel isolating and lonely. This tends to happen when I'm already feeling disconnected or when I crave social interaction and companionship. During these times, solitude can amplify feelings of sadness or restlessness, as it highlights the absence of close human connection and shared experiences.

The context in which I find myself alone also plays a significant role in shaping my perception. For example, being alone in a peaceful natural setting can evoke feelings of serenity and introspection, whereas being alone in a crowded city may intensify feelings of anonymity or detachment.

Time alone can be a healing experience when it is wanted but a terribly lonely one otherwise.

pending time alone can be a deeply personal and varied experience, influenced by an individual's personality, past experiences, and current life circumstances. For me, the experience of being alone can be both positive and negative, depending on the context and my state of mind.

Positive Aspects
Self-Reflection and Growth: Time alone allows for self-reflection and introspection. It provides an opportunity to think deeply about my life, my goals, and my relationships. This can lead to personal growth and a better understanding of myself.

Creativity and Productivity: Solitude often enhances my creativity and productivity. Without distractions, I can focus better and engage in creative activities such as writing, drawing, or brainstorming new ideas. This undisturbed time can be very fulfilling.

Peace and Relaxation: Being alone can be peaceful and relaxing. It gives me a break from the hustle and bustle of daily life and allows me to recharge. I can engage in activities that I find calming, such as reading, meditating, or taking a walk in nature.

Independence and Autonomy: Spending time alone reinforces my sense of independence. It reminds me that I can enjoy my own company and do things on my own without relying on others. This can be empowering and boost my confidence.

Negative Aspects
Loneliness and Isolation: On the flip side, extended periods of solitude can lead to feelings of loneliness and isolation. Humans are social beings, and too much time alone can make me feel disconnected from others, leading to sadness or even depression.

Overthinking and Anxiety: Sometimes, being alone gives me too much time to overthink and worry about various aspects of my life. This can lead to anxiety and negative thought patterns, especially if I'm dealing with stress or unresolved issues.

Lack of Social Interaction: Social interaction is important for mental health. When I spend too much time alone, I miss out on the benefits of socializing, such as shared experiences, laughter, and emotional support from friends and family.

Boredom: Without external stimulation, there are times when solitude can lead to boredom. If I'm not engaged in an activity, I might find myself feeling restless and seeking something to occupy my mind.

Conclusion
In summary, spending time alone is a complex experience with both positive and negative aspects. It provides valuable opportunities for self-discovery, creativity, and relaxation, but it can also lead to feelings of loneliness, overthinking, and boredom. Balancing alone time with social interaction is key to making the most of solitude and maintaining overall well-being.

No es positivo ni negativo. A veces uno necesita estar a solas y pensar en sus cosas mientras que otras se necesita la compañía de alguien más. Depende del momento y el lugar, y ambas situaciones son necesarias

creo que es muy positivo. Hay que saber estar solo, disfrutar de tus intereses y aficiones y no ser dependiente de los demás. Creo que los que creen que es algo netivo son demasiado dependientes y que hay tiempo para estar solo y para estar acompañado.
Yo creo que es importante pasar tiempo solo porque es cuando tienes tiempo en procesar y pensar en las cosas que te han ocurrido

Cuando estoy sola, tiendo a pensar en exceso, lo que intensifica mis preocupaciones y aumenta mi nivel de ansiedad. Lo que antes era una experiencia tranquila ahora puede convertirse en un momento de introspección abrumadora. En lugar de encontrar paz y claridad, a menudo me siento atrapado en un ciclo de pensamientos negativos que se vuelven difíciles de manejar.

Así que, aunque el tiempo a solas antes era algo que valoraba, en este momento, debido a mi ansiedad, no siempre me resulta positivo. Es un desafío encontrar un equilibrio entre disfrutar de la soledad y gestionar los pensamientos que surgen en esos momentos.

Nunca me aburro, nunca estoy parado. Al revés, me falta tiempo para hacer las cosas que quiero hacer, tanto de trabajo como relativo a mis aficiones, así que no le doy vueltas en mi cabeza al hecho de estar solo o no.

Para mí pasar tiempo solo es una experiencia positiva, porque es una soledad buscada. Me gusta tener tiempo para mí, para hacer lo que me apetezca, practicar mis aficiones. Suelo estar bastante a gusto a solas.

Creo que pasar tiempo solo,es positivo y necesario,ya quemnos ayuda a reflexionar sobre ciertas cosas aparte de ser una experiencia relajante,en definitiva creo que también ayuda a conocerse a uno mismo mejor

Para mi es una experiencia positiva porque me permite organizar mi vida y mis pensamiento. Me puedo conectar con mi mismo.

Como todo en la vida todo tiene un punto medio. No me gusta estar solo más de varios días, pero tampoco me gusta estar cada día socializando y haciendo planes, necesito tiempo también para mí. Aunque últimamente sí estar solo es un pensamiento más negativo.

Últimamente, pasar tiempo solo está siendo una parte fundamental para mí. Aunque siempre me gusta para tiempo con mis seres queridos, este tiempo que estoy pasando solo (por elección propia) me está sirviendo para hacer prácticas que me van a ser útiles en el futuro.

No creo que sea ni bueno ni malo. Hay muchas veces que me apetece de estar solo porque me gusta reflexionar sobre mis cosas. Tampoco me gusta hablar por hablar. Mucha gente cree que estar solo es ser síntoma de ser raro pero como dice el refrán más vale solo que mal acompañado
Para mi es positivo pasar tiempo solo, tiempo para reflexionar y valorar lo que es estar acompañado
Puede ser positivo para darte cuenta de tus necesidades como ser humano, todo el mundo quiere estar acompañado pero a veces no es posible, y al estar solo puedes ver lo que realmente quieres

Realmente me encuentro en un terreno neutro en cuanto a pasar tiempo sola. Depende del día y de cuanto hace que he hablado con alguien por última vez; si por ejemplo, acabo de venir de pasar unos días en casa de un amigo o de unas vacaciones con amigos, no me parece algo negativo el pasar tiempo sola una vez vuelvo a casa. Pero por otro lado, estarlo por un periodo de tiempo prolongado si que me perjudica mas a nivel mental y emocional.

Para mi estar solo puede ser positivo. Necesito diariamente tener un rato ( 1 hora / 2 horas) para mi. Para estar tranquila y para hacer mis cosas sin tener a nadie alrededor. Para mi estar es sano saber estar sola.

Hay veces que me gusta estar solo, se trata de un equilibrio, si estoy todo el día rodeado de gente y ajetreo necesito tener algo de tiempo yo solo, sin ningún "input" de nadie, y no mirar el móvil ni responder a nada siquiera.
Si llevo varios días que no salgo de casa y no hablo con nadie más que con mi familia por estar centrado en algún trabajo, se agradece salir y hablar con alguien de fuera.
Por lo tanto creo que estar algo de tiempo solo al menos una vez por semana es algo positivo, ya que ahí es donde te conoces a ti mismo.

Pasar tiempo solo para mí es una experiencia positiva porque es algo que yo hago conscientemente. Me explico: tengo gente a mi alrededor, sé que hay gente que me quiere y sé que hay gente que quiero. Dentro de este grupo de personas, me siento afortunado de saber que puedo recurrir a ellos para pasar el tiempo y sé que están ahí cuando los necesito. Sé que están a un mensaje de distancia o a una llamada de mí. Estar solo, para mí, por tanto, no es una realidad que tengo que afrontar porque no me queda otra. Es una elección que yo tomo porque disfruto estar solo, disfruto de los hobbies que tengo y que puedo practicar y realizar sin nadie más.

Estar solo siempre será una experiencia positiva cuando sea una elección que yo tomo voluntaria y conscientemente. Si estuviese solo porque no me queda otro remedio, posiblemente se convertiría en una experiencia negativa. Por ejemplo, en el confinamiento. Estar aislado y sin contacto físico porque no tenía más remedio sí tuvo un impacto negativo en mí. Pero hoy por hoy es una decisión y una acción que yo tomo porque puedo, y mientras sea así, será una sensación positiva.

Aunque a lo largo de mi vida he sentido que pasar tiempo sola a veces tenia partes malas, como sentirme distanciada, creo que mayormente es una experiencia positiva. Primero que todo porque soy una persona naturalmente introvertida y las interacciones sociales me cansan, así que pasar tiempo sola no me afecta tanto como a quienes pueden ser extrovertidos. Por otro lado creo que ese tiempo es una buena oportunidad para desarrollarme personalmente y saber exactamente qué cosas me gustan y cuáles son mis objetivos, sin influencia externa.
Es necesario tener algun momento solo cada semana porque ayuda a aclarar las ideas, a planear los siguientes pasos y a buscar soluciones a los problemas que vayan surgiendo.

Depende de mi estado mental. Si estoy en modo  autodestructivo pasar tiempo solo significa darle vueltas a pensamientos oscuros. Si estoy en una buena época me ayuda a gestionar mis emociones y a poner mi mente en orden

Para mi solo es una experiencia positiva. Rara vez lo veo con un haz de negatividad. Disfruto mucho de mi mismo y de actividades que se realizan en solitario. Aunque me guste estar con gente y demás, aprecio notablemente la paz, no tener que dar explicaciones a nadie, hacer lo que quiera en el momento que quiera, etc.

Es positivo porque me permite concentrarme en mis tareas sin distracciones o dedicarme a lo que me gusta durante un rato al dia. Ver series, jugar a videojuegos, ver o practicar deporte... no está mal estar solo de vez en cuando.
PARA MI ES POSITIVO PORQUE LO SUELO APROVECHAR PARA AFICIONES PERSONALES QUE NO PUEDO COMPARTIR CON OTRAS PERSONAS COMO LEER, ESCUCHAR MUSICA, NAVEGAR POR INTERNET, ETC.

Al teletrabajar paso la mayor tiempo sola en casa sin contacto social humano real, para mí es un poco negativo ya que necesito el relacionarme presencialmente para sentirme más feliz y a gusto. El pasar tiempo sola porque lo he decidido yo y no por ninguna condición es algo que beneficia a la persona a conocerse mejor y entender como funciona, eso es positivo.

Es una experiencia positiva y necesaria. Cuando comparto tiempo con la gente a menudo necesito aislarme y pasar tiempo en soledad para recuperar la energía. 

Es una ventaja ser solitario, aunque a veces te hace sentir un poco raro porque mucha gente no lo entiende. Disfruto de mi soledad en muchas ocasiones, comiendo en un restaurante, paseando, reflexionando... tengo conversaciones conmigo mismo y lo suelo pasar muy bien.
Me permite pensar en mis problemas

Pasar tiempo es importante porque en mi caso yo trabajo 8 horas cada dia y para mi pasar tiempo es positivo cuando paso con mi familia o amigos pero aveces es negativo cuando estoy aburrido y tengo nada para hacer pero ahora hago retratos y uso este tiempo para pasar mi tiempo en una manera positiva
Para mi es una experiencia muy positiva, me encanta pasar tiempo sola porque puedo hacer lo que me da la gana y realizar mis actividades favoritas tranquilamente.

Me encanta estar solo, aunque me describo como una persona extrovertida paso la mayoria de mi tiempo solo y eso es normal. Se tiene que saber vivir con uno mismo para ser feliz. Disfruto particularmente pasar largos ratos en la naturaleza haciendo deporte individualmente, me da paz interior.

Considero muy importante pasar tiempo a solas. Es necesario para invertir en uno mismo y adquirir un nivel de autoconciencia. Además estar constantemente rodeado de gente es un agotamiento energético del que hay que recuperarse pasando tiempo solo.

Pasar tiempos solo es una experiencia positiva porque te permite reflexionar sobre ti mismo y sobre tus circunstancias, permite hacer un ejercicio reflexivo sobre cómo te sientes y qué necesitas.  En mi opinión esto hace que uno se conozca mejor a sí mismo, siempre que el tiempo en soledad no sea angustioso o dañino. Pasar tiempo solos nos ayuda a tener un espacio propio y a conectar mejor con los demás.
Es una experiencia positiva porque puedo mirar en mi interior y estudiarme en que puedo mejorar
Para mi, pasar tiempo sola me da paz y no siento soledad. Me ayuda a conocerme y a desconectar del caos del dia a dia

Creo que depende mucho del tipo de persona que seas y lo que necesites. Hay gente a la que le gusta estar sola. Como a mí, por ejemplo, pero porque creo que las circunstancias me han 'obligado' a adaptarme a estar sola la mayor parte del tiempo, aunque esté acompañada. Me gusta hacer cosas solas antes que hacerlas con alguien que igual no comparte mi manera de ver las cosas o que sea muy diferente a mí, pero a veces tambien necesito ese contacto con alguien más. Pienso que la soledad es buena y todos necesitamos un poco de ella, pero no de manera excesiva.

Pasar tiempo solo es algo necesario para mí. Aunque disfruto mucho de socializar con mis amigos, al final del día me encuentro psicológicamente exhausto y necesito tiempo para mí para poder relajarme y dormir tranquilo. No obstante, periodos prolongados de soledad pueden conllevar efectos muy negativos en el estado de ánimo de una persona, por lo que creo que la soledad y la compañía deberían llevarse de una forma mutuamente compensada.
En mi opinion es una experiencia positiva porque ese tiempo lo puedo dedicar a hacer las actividades que me gustan sin que nadie me interrumpa
Ser una persona solitaria no tiene porqué significar algo negativo, siempre me he considerado así, disfruto la soledad y pasar tiempo en mis cosas.

LLevo mucho tiempo viviendo sola y me encanta, pasar tiempo solo te permite hacer las cosas que te gustan, dedicarte tiempo para ti mismo y cuando quieres quedas con amigos. Yi voy al cine sola, a conciertos, etc y lo recomiendo

A mi personalmente, el estar solo me provoca sensaciones mixtas. Por una parte, me encanta el tener tiempo para mi y tener tiempo de reflexión. Pero si estoy en público, prefiero siempre estar acompañado. Una excepción es viajar, me encanta viajar solo!

Yo aprecio mucho mi tiempo solo y me gusta organizar mi vida en soledad y hacer cosas que me aportan sin necesidad de nadie. En general es una experiencia positiva si te encuentras feliz o con una salud mental adecuada. Convivir con gente o socializar en general creo que puede ser beneficioso para otros casos y lo más importante es que tú mismo percibas que sea algo positivo. En mi caso no tengo problema con estar solo, vivo solo y es algo que realmente me gusta la mayor parte del tiempo. Si quiero socializar lo hago fuera de casa o puedo invitar a gente a casa, tengo lo mejor de ambos mundos

Pasar tiempo sola es positivo y negativo. Positivo en el sentido que puedes hacer todo lo que quieras contigo mismo y eso no es un problema, también te ayuda a conocerte mejor y aprender lo que realmente te gusta y quien realmente eres; a parte claro de poder ser más independiente y no depender de tener siempre a alguien para hacer algo.  Para mi personalmente lo negativo es que te acostumbras a esta dinámica y luego es difícil conectar con otras personas y dejarles un hueco en tu vida y tu tiempo.

He sido un hermitaño durante muchos años asi que conozco perfectamente los matices de estar en solitario.

La parte positiva es el tiempo para uno mismo, construir ideas, hobbies y progresar en la madurez, todo eso se realiza más eficientemente en solitario, a su vez ves todo con una perspectiva más calmada y segura.

Lo malo, puede tender a llevar a ideas negativas y destructivas, si es una persona pesimista o con falta de confianza acabas retroalimentando tu propia miseria personal, aunque no sea realista.

A mi me parece que estar solo es muy saludable ya que al no tener distracciones puedes hacer una introspección sobre ti, cosa que estando distraído es difícil de hacer. Además, estar aburrido es muy importante ya que de ahí surgen las mejores ideas.

En mi opinión, pasar tiempo solo te ayuda a reflexionar sobre ti mismo, tu comportamiento, tus objetivos, tu salud y es necesario hasta cierta medida siempre dependiendo de como es tu personalidad. En mi experiencia, aunque me gusta pasar tiempo solo, también necesito compartir mi tiempo con otra gente, bien deportes de equipo, charlar. Todo tiene sus puntos positivos y negativos, la clave está en el equilibrio. Por lo que la respuesta en resumen es una experiencia positiva siempre que se ajuste a tus necesidades.

Para mí, estar solo no significa lo mismo que sentirse solo. Que uno pase tiempo solo es importante por muchos motivos; es importante para conocerse a uno mismo, permite al cerebro descansar un poco de todo el ajetreo del día a día, etc. Sin embargo si te sientes solo y además pasas tiempo alejado de otras personas, ese sentimiento puede aumentar y hacerse más fuerte.
Valoro y necesito pasar tiempo solo. Me proporciona espacio para la reflexión y la introspección, lo que considero fundamental. No obstante, actualmente paso demasiado tiempo solo.

Creo que pasar tiempo solo puede ser positivo o negativo dependiendo de si lo hacemos por decision propia o no. En mi caso paso tiempo solo y me gusta hacerlo, me permite conectar conmigo mismo y las cosas que me gusta hacer a mi. Me sienta bien de tanto en tanto. Pero repito, en mi caso es algo que elijo yo. Quizás, si estuviera solo porque no tengo forma de estar con los demás (bien por exclusión social o cualquier otra circunstancia) estar solo no sería tan placentero.

Para mi es una experiencia positiva, vivo con mis padres pero paso mucho tiempo sola puesto que tengo que usar muchas horas estudiando, aun asi también me gusta tener ocio y salir a pasear sola por ejemplo, sobre todo cuando quiero reflexionar o desconectar cuando algo me preocupa. Al igual que tambien necesito pasar tiempo con mis amigos y mi familia, el tiempo sola para mi es igual de necesario para sentirme bien.

Para muchas personas puede resultar algo tranquilo para dedicarse tiempo a uno mismo o simplemente descansar, a mi personalmente me gusta más pasar mi tiempo en compañía de las personas que amo, me encantar conversar con mi pareja y amigos o jugar con mis hijos, prefiero pasar el tiempo rodeada de esas personas a estar sola, me siento mejor, en compañía y feliz
es una experiencia negativa debido a que no tienes a nadie que te respalde y te ayude en los momentos malos de tu vida
Para mi, pasar tiempo solo; me deja tiempo para pensar y llegar a un termino conmigo mismo. Puedo recargar mi batería social como alguien que sufre de ansiedad social.

Para mi, hay que tener tanto tiempo solo como social, y si me paso con uno o con el otro acabo sintiendome mal por motivos diferentes.

Sin tiempo y espacio para estar solo y tranquilo, me sobrecargo y me vuelvo mas irritable, pierdo mi paciencia al tratar con gente y generalmente me siento mas cansado.

Si no interactuo con amigos suficiente, me acabo sintiendo triste y me dejo llevar por mis pensamientos demasiado facilmente, causandome problemas emocionales. Hablar con amigos y tener un espacio para recordar que el mundo no es tan miserable como lo pinta es muy importante.
Es importante mencionar que tengo un diagnostico de autismo, asi que la forma en la que veo estas cosas es diferente a lo usual.

Pero bueno, en resumen, me gusta pasar tiempo a solas porque me ayuda a recargar la "bateria social".
Race_7_TEXT: Nacido en rumania, crecido mayormente en España

BeliefsOpen: Considero que pasar tiempo solo puede ser enriquecedor y en ocasiones necesario.Se necesita reflexionar y comprobar como cual es el estado de ánimo en estas circunstancias.

Pienso que pasar tiempo en solitario es bueno y malo a la vez. Te puede venir bien pasar tiempo a solas contigo mismo para saber que es lo que quieres y necesitas, y eso esta bien. Sin embargo, cuando te encuentras mal anímicamente o psicológicamente y necesitas de ayuda, estar suele puede ser contraproducente. Por lo que apoyarte en las personas de tu alrededor puede ser la mejor opción, obviamente siempre y cuando estas personas sean compresivas contigo y te apoyen.

Pienso que pasar tiempo solo no es que sea una experiencia positiva para mí, es que es necesaria. Es mi manera de cargar mis pilas. Estar con gente me supone un esfuerzo que termina por agotarme. Estar solo me permite dedicar tiempo a proyectos personales como escribir (llevo ya dos libros publicados) que, de otra manera, no podría llevar a cabo.

Depende de la situación, del momento, la persona, su estado de ánimo y su personalidad.  Hay personas que necesitan estar siempre rodeadas de gente y otras que son más solitarias. Estar a solas con uno mismo puede ser provechoso si sirve para reflexionar, meditar, realizar alguna actividad creativa que requiera mucha concentración. Es malo si uno se aisla de los demás permanentemente.

Personalmente, siempre he disfrutado del tiempo a solas. Considero que brinda la oportunidad de gestionar mejor la planificación del día a día y de invertir el tiempo en aquello que realmente hace feliz al individuo, sin restricciones más allá de las autoimpuestas. Para mí, se trata de poder disfrutar de lectura, escritura, edición, videojuegos, o actividades que prefiero realizar por mi cuenta.
No obstante, en ocasiones también me hace sentir que no aprecio las relaciones con los demás, lo cual evoca en mí sentimientos de culpabilidad.
Creo que pasar tiempo conmigo mismo es placenter, ya que me ayuda a concectar mas conmigo mismo y a conocerme mas.

Para mí, es una experiencia positiva porque soy una persona introvertida y hacer muchas actividades sociales me agota mentalmente. Gracias a pasar tiempo solo puedo hacer casi siempre lo que quiero y cuando quiero. Por otra parte, a veces es algo negativo porque me gustaría hacer algunas actividades acompañado, como ir a un restaurante a comer, y no siempre tengo la oportunidad de hacerlo.
Pasar tiempo a solas es algo bueno, puedes relajarte y no preocuparte por los demás. A veces es necesario desconectar de la gente y disfrutar de ti mismo.

Pasar tiempo solo es agradable, así me puedo dedicar a mí mismo. Lo malo sería pasar absolutamente toda la vida solo. Eso sería negativo, pero no es mi caso. Como decía, estar solo, si no es todo el tiempo, es agradable y positivo.
Pasar tiempo a solas es bueno para descansar,  recargar energías, para reflexionar, leer consentirse, escuchar nuestros pensamientos y así valorar más el tiempo que pasamos con otras personas.

Pasar tiempo sola es algo fundamental para mi. Necesito pasar mucho rato conmigo misma, y poder pensar y reflexionar si es que me apetece. Estar sola me ayuda a recargar mi batería social, que de normal es bastante baja, y así puedo aprovechar y hacer cosas que me gusten. Creo que pasar tiempo sola es muy beneficioso para mi.

Para mi, pasar tiempo solo no es malo, porque no es lo mismo pasar tiempo solo, que pasar tiempo en soledad. Pasar tiempo solo puede servir para reflexionar y descubrir cosas que antes no sabias que te gustaban, hacer cosas nuevas sin tener que esperar a nadie, ni depender de nadie, y poder conocerse a si mismo

Para mí es algo neutral, ni positivo ni negativo, me gusta relacionarme con gente, pero también pienso que saber estar a solas es importante, ya que no siempre vas a tener a alguien contigo en todo momento. Así como aprender a entretenerte o hacer algo productivo sin depender de nadie.

Desde que empecé a crecer como adolescente he estado solo, por lo que he normalizado el estar la mayor parte de mi tiempo en soledad. Positivamente me ha ayudado a conocer mis gustos personales, descubrir aficiones que puedo desarrollar por mí mismo y depender de mí a la hora de levantarme emocionalmente. En cambio, la soledad también trae consigo el no tener un referente o una opinión que difiera para crecer personal y críticamente, por lo que a veces hay golpes de realidad muy duros cuando no se ven venir, y cuesta recuperarse.

Me gusta mucho pasar tiempo solo, me ayuda a pensar, reflexionar y filosofar.
Me gusta tener un buen equilibrio entre estar solo y acompañado.
Casi nunca puedo pasar tiempo solo en el trabajo o en casa con la familia, así que me gusta aprovechar las ocasiones en que ocurre para relajarme y hacer cosas diferentes.

En mi caso particular, pasar tiempo sola es una experiencia muy positiva. Tengo tiempo para dedicarme a mi, a mis aficiones e intereses, sin nadie que me interrumpa, moleste o presione, sin nadie a quien atender o cuidar. Me permite descansar del estrés que me supone estar rodeada de gente y desconectar. Como único punto negativo, me cuesta empezar tareas si estoy sola a falta del refuerzo del "body doubling".
Yo lo encuentro beneficial, me da tiempo de hacer cosas, relajarme un poco, eschuchar musica con bastante volumen

Creo que estar solo en segunda que casos, es positivo. Te permite desconectar del estrés, practicar tus aficiones e ir a tu propio ritmo. Aunque, a veces, se echa en falta esa compañía que te dan los amigos al socializar y te hace sentir aislado del mundo exterior. Depende del dia; hay veces que te gusta estar solo y otros que detestas esa soledad.

Para mí pasar tiempo solo es una experiencia positiva, me permite gestionar mi entorno y mis emociones. Considero que pasar tiempo con otra gente es beneficioso e intento combinarlo con el hecho de pasar tiempo solo, pero creo que el hecho de compartir espacio con otra gente desgasta mi energía. Cuando estoy solo estoy en equilibrio y no tengo preocupaciones.

Normalmente pienso que es una experiencia positiva porque me deja reflexionar sobre muchas cosas y me permite manejar el tiempo de forma más adaptable, sin embargo es cierto que esto hace que cada vez te aísles más debido a que te acostumbras y no sientes la necesidad de ser tan social o encajar con el resto, cosa que supone un problema a la larga. Lo correcto sería administrar la forma en la que uno pasa el tiempo para evitar lo dicho anteriormente y así disfrutar de las dos cosas.

De momento para mí, pasar algo de tiempo solo es positivo, porque me supone tiempo para mí mismo: puedo leer, escuchar música, reflexionar.
Sé que además va a ser poco tiempo, por lo que intento aprovecharlo.
Hay momentos donde pasar tiempo solo te permita refrescar tu mente y relajarte. Para mi es una experiencia positiva.

Ahora mismo estoy en un momento de mi vida en el que pienso que necesito tener tiempo para mi y para estar conmigo misma porque me he malacostumbrado mucho a estar siempre con mi pareja y a veces siento que necesito alejarme porque se que me viene bien para estar mas en paz conmigo misma. Sin embargo es muy cierto que soy una persona que prefiere disfrutar de las experiencias acompañada y no sola, y ademas muchas veces me siento sola y aislada incluso de la gente a mi alrededor. Asi que yo diria que pasar tiempo sola/solo es necesario y positivo para ti mismo pero a la vez es negativo porque puede llevarte a sentirte solo y desplazado de la gente.

Depende de si es una elección voluntaria o no.
Personalmente, en ocasiones puede ser una experiencia negativa cuando quiero pasar tiempo con alguien y no tengo a quien recurrir.

Pasar tiempo solo me ayuda a ordenar mis pensamientos y sentirme con más energía. Es como volver a una zona segura en la que puedo apartar mis preocupaciones y hacer cosas que me gustan. Sin embargo, creo que en exceso puede ser perjudicial porque puede alejarte de tus obligaciones y puedes perder muchas oportunidades para mejorar como persona. Creo que la clave está en dedicarte tiempo para estar contigo mismo en días estresantes, pero no utilizar cada día largos momentos de soledad para lidiar con el estrés cuando, por ejemplo, podrías estar durmiendo.

Soy una persona bastante introvertida así que me gusta pasar tiempo sola para recargar mi batería social. Estoy a gusto conmigo misma y realmente hay muchas actividades que me gusta hacer sola como ir de compras, ir al cine, etc. Para mí es una experiencia positiva, aunque a veces, al pasar mucho tiempo sola, puedes sentirte solo también, y eso ya es otra cosa. Empiezas a pensar que no tienes a nadie que te acompañe a hacer ciertas cosas aunque te guste hacerlo sola igualmente, es como que no tienes la opción de pedirle a alguien que te acompañe.

Creo que es positivo para me ayuda a encontrar ideas creativas y poder trabajar en mis cosas sin prisas y con cabeza y tranquilidad. Soy musico y suelo componer canciones solo, y es muy diferente de hacerlo en el local con la banda, con todas las prisas y necesidad de sacar algo bueno que le gusta a los demas. Cuando estoy solo puedo desarollar y buscar ideas mas atrevidas y hacerlo sin tapujos.

 Me gusta pasar tiempo solo leyendo y absorviendo informacion, la cual luego la comparto con la gente cuando socializo. Yo creo que estar solo te ayuda a desarollar tu persona, ser mas interestante, mas culto y crecer como persona. Hacerlo con la ayuda de la gente tambien es bueno y positivo, pero de diferente manera. Yo creo que las dos cosas tienen que estar equilibradas para ser un ser humano sano y feliz.

Para mi es una experiencia positiva ya que pasar tiempo solo me ayuda a saber conocerme y saber las emociones que tengo en ese momento. Es muy importante también para poder reflexionar sobre quién soy y los valores que tengo.
Otra parte positiva es que puedo relajare después de un día ajetreado en el trabajo.
Hay aspectos negativos si no sabes crear un equilibrio en el tiempo que pasas solo, ya que puede convertirse en algo continuo y esto generar sentimientos de soledad que llevan a la depresión y ansiedad.
Hay momentos y situaciones en las que prefiero estar solo y poder pensar y decidir lo que voy a hacer o lo que me gustaría que pasara y como afrontarlo

Me encanta y disfruto enormemente de los momentos de soledad. Es cuando puedo dedicarme a mí misma, hacer lo que verdaderamente deseo, sin situaciones forzadas por lo que puedan querer o esperar de mí los demás. Es ahí cuando me siento yo misma. Cuando hago lo que quiero. Quizá la soledad absoluta no sea buena, pero no es mi caso. Siempre tengo gente alrededor. Por eso disfruto tanto de mis momentos a solas conmigo misma.

Pasar tiempo solo me da la oportunidad de recargarme y reflexionar sin distracciones. A menudo disfruto de la calma y la independencia y encuentro que esos momentos me ayudan a conocerme mejor. Sin embargo, a veces también me siento un poco desconectado o solo, especialmente si pasa mucho tiempo sin interacción social. En general, valoro estos momentos de soledad como una forma de crecimiento personal y autocomprensión.

Realmente depende. Estar solo es algo positivo si te sientes sobrecargado de la compañía, si prefieres estar invirtiendo tiempo de calidad en ti mismo o si simplemente necesitas desconectas. Estar solo puede también ser algo terriblemente negativo en algunos casos, como por dar un ejemplo, que estés pasando un mal momento y no tengas gente a tu alrededor para procesarlo o salir adelante de ello. Todo depende de la circunstancia.
Para mí es una experiencia positiva porque pasas tiempo contigo mismo y desconectas un poco de tanto estímulo constante al que estamos expuestos hoy en día.

Aunque soy consciente de los beneficios que puede tener estar solo, debido a las condiciones de mi vida actualmente no disfruto de estar "solo", la paso evadiendome en redes sociales y concentrado en el trabajo.
Considero que estar solo te sirve para conocerte mas a ti mismo, que te gusta hacer, también para no depender emocionalmente de otras personas y ser mas independiente
pasar tiempo solo es una experiencia positiva porque me ayuda a reflexionar y conocerme a mi mismo

Creo que es una experiencia positiva porque estando sólo te descubres a ti mismo, descubres como eres y tu forma de pensar, e incluso te das cuenta de la manera en la que interaccionas con los demas. Es positivo siempre y cuando no sea mucho tiempo.

Pasar tiempo sola permite reflexionar en mis pensamientos y/o preocupaciones. Para mí es una experiencia positiva porque aprendo a no depender de compañía para sentirme bien y no siento presión para socializar como cuando suele ocurrir al estar con otras personas.
Asimismo, estar sola me deja hacer las cosas que yo quiero y me gustan, sin conflicto con otros por elegir qué hacer. 
Sin embargo, estar solo/a no debe ser algo que ocurra siempre, sino debería haber un poco de equilibrio junto a la opción de estar en compañía.

ME GUSTA PASAR TIEMPO A SOLAS, ES MÁS NO VIVO CON NADIE Y NO CREO QUE PUEDA. ESTOY BIEN SOLO. 
HECHO DE MENOS A PERSONAS PARA CONTARLES LAS COSAS BUENAS QUE PASAN Y LAS MALAS
SÍ NO HAY NADIE TAMPOCO PASA NADA

Pasar tiempo solo puede ser una experiencia bastante enriquecedora, pero siempre que sea un experiencia elegida. La soledad forzada es una experiencia bastante desagradable porque te sientes forzado, coartado a estar estar sin ningún tipo de compañía. Creo que esta es la peor soledad, la cual veo a menudo en personas mayores. 
Creo que hay un tipo de soledad de la que poco se habla, que es la soledad de las actividades laborales. Muchas veces al trabajar pese que lo hacemos con compañeros, estamos sumidos en una soledad individualizada. Cada uno de nosotros está haciendo una actividad, pero no compartimos más que el espacio. De este tipo de soledad creo que es de la que más tengo. 

Sin embargo, también creo que hay unas soledades que peuden ser posivitas e incluso enriquecedoras, ya que permiten escuchar(te) y conocerte un poco más. No obstante también creo que nos da tanto miedo este tipo de soledad que intententamos rellenar esos espacios de soledad con estílumos placenteros como series, tiktoks, o cosas así.

A veces es un poco triste, pero la realidad es que me gusta. A veces no me siento cómoda con mucha vida social, estar con amigos me cansa mental y fisicamente, mi familia a veces puede ser demandante y mi pareja con la que vivo, aunque me encanta estar con el, también me demanda tiempo y no me deja disfrutar de la casa como me gustaría.
Para mi es una experiencia positiva porque recargo energía, me permite hacer introspección, conectar conmigo misma.
para mí pasar tiempo solo significa libertad de movimiento y de pensamiento, me tranquiliza y lo necesito para trabajar con el ordenador

Al menos para mi personalidad, pasar tiempo solo me permite estar relajado, realizar ciertas tareas con concentración  y, sin pensar en ser interrumpido en ese momento. Otras veces son buenos momentos para reflexionar sobre cualquier cosa, ya sea importante o por puro entretenimiento. Sin estos momentos durante el día, me puedo ver más cansado y, con la necesidad de disfrutar de lo anteriormente dicho al día siguiente.

Pasar tiempo solo es algo para mí también positivo, ya que viene bien dedicarse tiempo a uno mismo, poder desconectar de lo que te rodea. Es tiempo para relarse y hacer lo que te apetece o necesitas sin nada más que te pueda perturbar. Lo ideal es poder compaginar tiempo solo con tiempo con otras personas. Pasar demasiado tiempo solo si que se convierte en algo megativo, sobre todo si no tienes más remedio que estar en esa situación.

Creo que pasar tiempo sola no solo es positivo sino que es necesario. Da igual que esté en pareja o soltera, siempre necesito pasar algo de tiempo sola como parte de mi vida diaria, y también ir de vacaciones sola de vez en cuando. Es necesario para tener un poco de espacio para reflexionar, para hacer lo que me apetezca, hasta para aburrirme sola un poco- es tiempo de autoconocimiento fundamental.

Estar solo no me parece una experiencia negativa, lo contrario, me encanta estar solo ya que uso este tiempo para hacer mis hobbies/pasatiempos. Me da tiempo a pensar, reflexionar y planificar, cosas que normalmente no prefiero hacer en compañía.
